To fully characterize the performance of our inkjet-printed PDs, their figures of merit were computed, such as R, D, EQE, ON/OFF ratio, and wavelength λ-dependent transport, as shown by the data in Fig. 4a–d. Figure 4a provides the dependence of R as a function of light intensity F for both Gr- and Ag-contacted PDs at T ~ 300 K and biased at 40 V. Here, the R is determined using:5R=JphF\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
